; one-acceleration-engine.form — ONE shared JIT lowering pipeline for every kernel,
; replacing the three bespoke per-kernel JITs. The north star Urs named:
;
;   "How is shrinking helping with float JIT support? Unify all the JIT lowerings
;    with a single working pipeline." (2026-06-19)
;
; ── THE PROBLEM: three JITs are three divergence surfaces ──
;   Each kernel today lowers a hot closure to native in ITS OWN host language:
;     - Go   : recipe → Go source → `go build -buildmode=plugin` → plugin.Open   (jit.go)
;     - Rust : recipe → Rust source → `rustc --crate-type=cdylib` → libloading    (main.rs)
;     - TS   : recipe → MSL/WGSL/CUDA via the GPU emitters                         (backends/)
;   Three emitters, three compilers, three ABIs. Float bit-identity must then be won
;   THREE times against THREE optimizers — and it is not. The Go float JIT lets the
;   host compiler fuse a*b+c into a single-rounding FMA (or reorder a reduction), so
;   the native body is NOT bit-identical to the walk. The async JIT adopts that body
;   MID-FOLD, so a float-accumulating training loop uses walk-floats before adoption
;   and native-floats after — the final weights depend on WHEN the background build
;   landed. MEASURED (2026-06-19): the neural-lm-corpus band (a real-corpus bigram LM)
;   read go=5 while rust=ts=fkwu=7, nondeterministically — a band that would pass
;   four-way most runs and randomly diverge. The four-way floor caught it.
;   Shrinking the Go JIT to i64-only "fixes" this by DELETING float JIT (slow-walk) —
;   a stopgap pointed away from the goal. The goal is float JIT that WORKS.
;
; ── THE INSIGHT: only a SHARED, bit-identical-BY-CONSTRUCTION lowering is correct ──
;   Bit-identity chased per-compiler is a losing game. Bit-identity by CONSTRUCTION is
;   already solved, in one place, as a Form recipe:
;     - jit-tensor-emit.fk — the emitter is a FORM RECIPE (host keeps only the dumb
;       carriers: clang/rustc, dlopen, call-by-pointer). It is bit-identical by
;       construction: the inner loop accumulates j DOWN exactly like tb-dot's
;       right-fold, and mul/add split through a NAMED TEMPORARY so "no conformant
;       compiler can contract them into an fma." MEASURED: native = recipe to the last
;       bit, 20,077× on a 1280² matvec; the MSL lanes bit-exact vs the CPU reference in
;       the lane's own conversion chain (scripts/metal_matvec_audit.sh).
;     - fkwu's SELF-JIT — the one already in the body. hati-os-kernel-emit.fk's
;       "self-JIT on heat" lowers each pure function FROM ITS CELLS to a native fk_nat
;       (fkc-nat-expr / fkc-emit-jit); the emitted walker counts heat per function and
;       FLIPS dispatch to the native past a threshold (fk_njit probe); melt-hot-swap
;       melts a cold native back to the walk, champion-challenger gated with THE WALK AS
;       THE ALWAYS-CORRECT CHAMPION. The native is emitted from the same cells and the
;       walk stays the reference, so it is bit-identical by construction — the same
;       discipline jit-tensor-emit proves at tensor scale (named-temp, no fma contraction).
;       This IS a full JIT, 100% in Form, inside the universal walker.
;
; ── THE ONE ENGINE: fkwu's self-JIT, extended to floats ──
;   The unified pipeline is not a new thing to build beside fkwu — it is fkwu's OWN
;   self-JIT. Front-end: flatten a function's cells (already done). Engine: emit fk_nat
;   from the cells, heat-flip to native, melt cold natives back, walk-as-champion
;   (already done for the pure-compute INTEGER family — tags 1-7, 12; fk_nat is long long).
;   Because every kernel runs fkwu, ONE self-JIT serves all four — no Go-plugin,
;   Rust-cdylib, or TS bespoke emitter needed.
;   THE ONE GAP (Urs, 2026-06-19 — "fkwu has a full JIT, 100% in fkwu, and if not, that
;   is what we need"): the self-JIT does not yet lower FLOATS. The WALK handles floats
;   fully (the float arms box fk_fbox(fk_num(a) op fk_num(b)) — the bit-identical
;   reference); fk_nat does not. Closing it: fkc-nat-expr gains float arms emitting
;   fk_fbox(<f64 expr over fk_num(a)>) THROUGH NAMED TEMPORARIES (never a*b+c in one C
;   expression, so clang cannot contract to an fma), a boxed fk_natf table, the
;   heat-walker dispatching it, and the honesty gate (fkc-can-list) widened to the
;   float-pure family. The native then runs the EXACT fk_num/fk_fbox/f64 sequence the
;   walk runs → bit-identical by construction, unlike the Go f64 plugin.
;   For tensor-shaped hot paths the jit-tensor-emit C/MSL lane is the same discipline at
;   width (native = recipe bit-for-bit, 20,077×) — the self-JIT's vectorized face, not a
;   separate engine.
;
; ── THE MIGRATION (each step provable; the integer self-JIT is the proven template) ──
;   M0  FLOAT SELF-JIT IN fkwu — the one real gap. Extend fkc-nat-expr + fkc-emit-jit to
;       the float-pure family with named-temp emission; prove a float-pure function
;       heat-flips to a native that equals the walk bit-for-bit (hati_os_kernel_audit.sh).
;       This is what makes float JIT correct AND fast AND shared — the answer to the
;       neural-lm-corpus divergence, in fkwu, not in a bespoke host plugin. (JIT_GAP_LEDGER #11.)
;       M0 has TWO native targets and the truly sovereign one is the CLANG-FREE byte path
;       (form-asm/form-lower/form-macho — clang only the byte-identity oracle), not the
;       C-emit fkc-nat-expr lane (which compiles its C through clang). LANDED 2026-06-19:
;       the FLOAT-encoding FOUNDATION of that byte path — the arm64 scalar-double FPDP tier
;       (fadd/fsub/fmul/fdiv/fsqrt/fmov/fcmp/scvtf/fcvtzs/ldr-d/str-d) as DATA rows in
;       form-asm.fk, every encoding clang-ORACLE-verified byte-for-byte, form-asm-float
;       → 2047 FOUR-WAY incl. fkwu (JIT_GAP_LEDGER #12). REMAINING: form-lower float
;       lowering (FP register stack + d0..d7 calling convention) then wiring the self-JIT
;       heat-flip through form-lower→form-asm BYTES — float native with NO clang in the path.
;       KEYSTONE 2026-06-21: the FP register stack was blocked by form-lower's fa-conviction
;       being WHOLE-FUNCTION byte-identity to clang — matching clang's register allocation is
;       the oracle-as-MASTER ceiling (allocation has many valid lowerings; only an instruction's
;       encoding has one true answer). form-lower-sim.fk (fsim) lifts it: a 32-register arm64 FP
;       machine in Form EXECUTES a lowered sequence and validates allocation by execution-
;       equivalence with the source, keeping byte-identity only per-instruction. form-lower-sim
;       → 15 FOUR-WAY. LANDED 2026-06-21: lo-ftree (form-lower.fk) — the abstract float lowering with the
;       two non-ARG subtree register stack (caller-saved d16+), correctness by fsim execution, byte-
;       consistent with lo-fnode on the single-arg overlap. form-lower-fp-stack → 31 FOUR-WAY — the first
;       op-coverage growth on the no-clang float lane past single-arg, no clang allocation rented. REMAINING
;       for M0: unify lo-fnode onto lo-ftree (one lowering), then wire the self-JIT heat-flip through bytes.
;   M1  Host hot-paths dispatch to the in-process fkwu self-JIT instead of emitGoExpr→
;       go-build / the Rust cdylib emitter. TestFkwuOffloadBridge is the proven seed; the
;       open work is a Go/Rust kernel INTEGRATION task (fast in-process invocation), not
;       an fkwu gap.
;   M2  Rust and TS hot-paths dispatch to the same self-JIT. Three bespoke emitters → one.
;   M3  The jit-tensor-emit C/MSL vectorized face generalizes from matvec/train shapes to
;       the closure families the walk identifies as hot, shared by all kernels.
;   M4  Compost emitGoExpr (jit.go), the Rust cdylib emitter, and the bespoke TS path —
;       once dispatch is unified, three host-language emitters are duplicated tissue.
;
; ── OWNED + TRACKED (not buried) ──
;   The neural-lm-corpus band (real-corpus bigram LM, beats the unigram baseline) is
;   CORRECT on fkwu/rust/ts (7); the lone diverger is the Go BESPOKE float JIT (an
;   optimization path, not the walk). Per the four-way rule the divergence is
;   root-caused (host-compiler FMA on the non-bit-identical float plugin, adopted
;   mid-fold) and tracked HERE to its specific fix: M0 above (fkwu's float self-JIT —
;   the bit-identical native that makes the bespoke plugin unnecessary). The band stays
;   out of form/fourth-arm-bands.txt until that lands — owned, named, not silently
;   omitted. The FORM_JIT_HOT knob (jit.go) lets a workload run the deterministic walk meanwhile.
;
; KIN: jit-tensor-emit.fk (the emitter-as-recipe, bit-identical by construction) ·
;   form/form-kernel-go/fkwu_bridge_test.go (the in-process offload bridge, proven) ·
;   hati-os-kernel-emit.fk (fkwu's C emitted by Form) · hati-os-native-cli-emit.fk
;   (emit→clang→exec) · form-native-models.form (the JIT-realization-gap note: the
;   in-process Go plugin dispatch never realized a speedup either — the emit-compile-exec
;   lane is the honest fast path) · neural-lm.fk + scripts/form_cli_neural_lm_train.sh
;   (the real-corpus LM whose four-way run exposed the divergence).
; teaching: lc-cognitive-sovereignty
